This python project uses OOPS, MySql, and if - else condition concepts to view, insert, delete or update data into the database. The database already consists of some sample data. Here, menu driven approach is utilised for user - convenience.

How to run the code on local machine:
1. Install MySql from [here](http://dev.mysql.com/downloads/)
2. Start MySql command prompt.
3. Enter the command - create database restaurant;
4. Enter the command - use restaurant;
5. Minimize the MySql command prompt.
6. Copy the code and paste it into a new python IDLE file. For python installation check [here](https://www.python.org/downloads/)
7. Press F5 and that's it.
